The paper deals with wireless resource allocation problems, specifically power control in interference channels. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed method utilizes graph neural networks (GNNs), which are a type of deep learning model, and thus falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the performance of the proposed method in terms of speedup over existing algorithms, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
